[0m[32m[TOOL][0m [32m+
[0m[32m[TOOL][0m [32m+%description
[0m[32m[TOOL][0m [32m+Module::Runtime provides several routines which might come in handy if you were
[0m[32m[TOOL][0m [32m+doing things at runtime (at run time) that involve modules, and you couldn't do
[0m[32m[TOOL][0m [32m+them at compile time. This includes inspecting the name of the current module or
[0m[32m[TOOL][0m [32m+the package of an object, converting a string containing a class or package name
[0m[32m[TOOL][0m [32m+into its canonical form (e.g., 'Some::Class' -> 'Some/Class.pm'), loading a
[0m[32m[TOOL][0m [32m+module and checking if it loaded successfully, returning all the names of
[0m[32m[TOOL][0m [32m+modules currently loaded, verifying if something is a valid module, returning
[0m[32m[TOOL][0m [32m+the path in @INC where a module was found, and other things.
